# Docker-Only Development Environment

- Run all development, build, test, lint, formatting, migration, and code-generation commands inside project Docker containers.
- Do not install language runtimes, SDKs, package managers, databases, brokers, or build tools on the host machine.
- Do not use host tools such as `brew`, `pip install`, `npm install`, Gradle, Android SDK, `uv`, or database clients for project work.
- Host commands are limited to Docker/Docker Compose, Git, and basic repository inspection.
- Define required tooling in Dockerfiles and invoke it through `docker compose run`, `docker compose exec`, or documented wrapper scripts.
- If a required container does not exist, add or update the project Docker configuration instead of installing the tool locally.
- Keep dependency versions reproducible through lockfiles and pinned container image versions.

## Examples

```bash
# Correct
docker compose run --rm control-plane uv run pytest
docker compose run --rm android ./gradlew test

# Incorrect
uv run pytest
./gradlew test
brew install android-platform-tools
```
